%2Farticles%2Fcdez8x693wko%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcdez8x693wko.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcdez8x693wko.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Monsoon%20Gardening%3A%20Grow%20Tangy%20Karonda%20(Indian%20Cranberry)%20in%206%20Easy%20Steps%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESunday%20mornings%20were%20magical%20for%20me%20as%20a%20child.%20The%20highlight%20was%20my%20%3Cem%3Ebaba%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(grandfather)%20trip%20to%20the%20local%20vegetable%20market.%20Every%20return%20brought%20a%20familiar%20joy%20I%20yearned%20for%20%E2%80%94%20a%20new%20batch%20of%20fresh%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20greens%20and%20potatoes%20in%20his%20old%20%3Cem%3Ejhola%20%3C%2Fem%3E(bag)%2C%20there%20were%20the%20treasures%20I%20sought%3A%20%3Cem%3Ekaronda%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Indian%20cranberry)%2C%20small%20and%20jewel-like%20fruits%20in%20green%20and%20red%20hues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIgnoring%20my%20%3Cem%3Eamma%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20(grandmother)%20gentle%20prompt%20to%20wash%20them%20first%2C%20I%E2%80%99d%20dive%20right%20in%20to%20taste%20the%20mouthwatering%20tartness.%20The%20karonda%E2%80%99s%20burst%20of%20flavour%20was%20pure%20delight%20%E2%80%94%20a%20flavour%20that%20lingered%20in%20our%20afternoon%20meals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmma%20transformed%20these%20berries%20into%20tangy%20chutneys.%20Surplus%20harvests%20were%20pickled%2C%20preserving%20the%20summer%E2%80%99s%20bounty%20to%20enhance%20meals%20long%20after%20the%20season%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaronda%20has%20spread%20joy%20across%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20best%20part%3F%20It%20is%20easily%20grown%20at%20home.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20your%20guide%20to%20cultivating%20this%20hardy%2C%20drought-tolerant%20fruit%20during%20the%20monsoon%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20Choosing%20your%20propagation%20method%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaronda%20can%20be%20grown%20from%20seeds%2C%20cuttings%2C%20or%20air%20layering.%20During%20monsoon%2C%20both%20cuttings%20and%20air%20layering%20can%20be%20successful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20cuttings%2C%20take%20semi-hardwood%20cuttings%20(about%2025-30%20cm%20long).%20Whereas%20air%20layering%20method%20involves%20inducing%20roots%20to%20form%20on%20a%20branch%20while%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20attached%20to%20the%20parent%20plant.%20The%20rooted%20air%20layers%20are%20ready%20for%20transplanting%20after%20about%20three%20and%20a%20half%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99re%20propagating%20from%20seeds%2C%20sow%20them%20in%20August%20or%20September%20for%20better%20germination%20and%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Preparing%20the%20soil%20and%20planting%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F454949%2Fmonsoon-kitchen-garden-guide-grow-your-vegetables-and-herbs-monsoon-season-temperature-soil%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DStep%252Dby%252Dstep%2520guide%2520to%2Cgood%2520air%2520circulation%2520around%2520plants.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonsoon%20season%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20a%20good%20time%20for%20planting.%20Choose%20a%20spot%20that%20receives%20plenty%20of%20sunlight%2C%20and%20ensure%20the%20soil%20is%20well-drained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fkaronda-1-1753091410.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Harvest%20when%20the%20fruits%20are%20fully%20red%20and%20slightly%20soft%20to%20the%20touch.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fkaronda-1-1753091410.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fkarond